 {"id":"frankentorch-tdqo","title":"tensor_cdist severs autograd; broadcastable composition for finite p > 0","description":"tensor_cdist at lib.rs:4230 computes pairwise L_p distances between two sets of vectors. For finite p > 0 the math is composable through autograd-aware primitives via broadcasted subtraction.\n\nStrategy for shape [P, M] x [R, M]:\n  x1_b = unsqueeze(x1, 1)    → [P, 1, M]\n  x2_b = unsqueeze(x2, 0)    → [1, R, M]\n  diff = x1_b - x2_b         → [P, R, M] (broadcast)\n  d    = (sum_k |diff[k]|^p)^(1/p)\n\nFor batched [B, P, M] x [B, R, M] the same pattern works at dims 2 and 1.\n\nSister of frankentorch-0i8u (pdist). p == 0 / p == +inf still fail-loud on requires_grad.","notes":"Fixed in this commit. Composed tensor_cdist through unsqueeze + expand + sub + abs + pow + sum_dim + pow primitives for both 2-D and 3-D batched inputs. The broadcasted subtraction handles both [P, M] x [R, M] and [B, P, M] x [B, R, M] cases. p == 0 / p == +inf still fail-loud on requires_grad to make autograd severance explicit (deferred to a follow-up — same pattern as pdist 0i8u). Added cdist_l2_propagates_gradient_through_both_inputs regression test (single-pair x1=[[0,0]], x2=[[3,4]], p=2 → grad_x1=[-3/5,-4/5], grad_x2=[3/5,4/5]). ft-api lib tests: 1170.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-30T22:37:23.580514506Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-30T22:39:43.808185068Z","closed_at":"2026-04-30T22:39:43.804679425Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"frankentorch-tf10","title":"[parity-gap] ft-api missing tensor_addcmul / tensor_addcdiv","description":"Deep-review (StormyBirch 2026-05-20): ft-api exposes 398 tensor_* ops but has no tensor_addcmul or tensor_addcdiv. torch.addcmul(input, t1, t2, value=1) = input + value*t1*t2 and torch.addcdiv(input, t1, t2, value=1) = input + value*t1*t2.recip() are public torch ops (also in-place addcmul_/addcdiv_) used widely in optimizer update rules and elementwise fused math. Both are trivially composable through existing autograd-aware primitives (tensor_mul/tensor_div/tensor_add + a scalar) so they can be added to ft-api without kernel/dispatch work, like the var/std correction rescale. Verified absent: no 'addcmul'/'addcdiv' anywhere in crates/ft-api or ft-optim; 0 hits in issues.jsonl. Acceptance: tensor_addcmul/tensor_addcdiv (+ tensor_addcmul_/tensor_addcdiv_ if in-place is wanted), autograd-correct, with focused ft-api regressions and a torch 2.12 differential check.","status":"closed","priority":3,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-05-20T09:28:35.052411855Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-05-20T09:31:44.591518049Z","closed_at":"2026-05-20T09:31:44.591282573Z","close_reason":"Implemented tensor_addcmul/tensor_addcdiv in ft-api, composed through autograd-aware primitives. Verified vs torch 2.12. Commit 1c13f3d.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
