 {"id":"frankentorch-tk5","title":"Enrich Module register_parameter/register_buffer errors with module type context","description":"## Context\nThe stub/placeholder audit (2026-04-02) found that Module::register_parameter() and Module::register_buffer() default implementations (ft-nn/src/lib.rs) return `Err(ModuleRegistrationError::Unsupported { operation: \"register_parameter\" })`.\n\nThe error tells you WHAT operation failed but not WHICH module rejected it. When debugging a deep Sequential model with 50+ layers, \"register_parameter unsupported\" gives no clue about which layer is the problem.\n\n## Current error type\n```rust\npub enum ModuleRegistrationError {\n    InvalidName { kind: &'static str },\n    NameConflict { name: String },\n    Unsupported { operation: &'static str },\n}\n```\n\n## Design decision: How to get the module type name in a trait default\n\nThe trait default method signature is `fn register_parameter(&mut self, ...)`. We CANNOT call `std::any::type_name::<Self>()` because the default method has `Self: ?Sized` (it's on `dyn Module`).\n\n**Solution**: Add a new required method to the Module trait:\n```rust\nfn module_type_name(&self) -> &'static str;\n```\nThis is cheap (one &'static str per impl), gives correct type info even through dyn dispatch, and follows the same pattern PyTorch uses with `_get_name()`.\n\nEach module implementation returns its name: \"Linear\", \"Conv2d\", \"Sequential\", etc.\n\nThe default for register_parameter/register_buffer then becomes:\n```rust\nfn register_parameter(...) -> Result<(), ModuleRegistrationError> {\n    Err(ModuleRegistrationError::Unsupported {\n        operation: \"register_parameter\",\n        module_type: self.module_type_name(),\n    })\n}\n```\n\n## Plan\n1. Add `module_type_name(&self) -> &'static str` to the Module trait (no default — every impl must provide it)\n2. Add `module_type: &'static str` field to `ModuleRegistrationError::Unsupported`\n3. Update the Display impl to print \"{module_type} does not support {operation}\"\n4. Update default register_parameter/register_buffer to include module_type\n5. Add `module_type_name()` to ALL existing Module implementations (~40+ structs):\n   - Linear -> \"Linear\", Conv1d -> \"Conv1d\", Sequential -> \"Sequential\", etc.\n6. Update any tests that construct or match ModuleRegistrationError::Unsupported\n\n## Testing requirements\n\n### Unit tests (in ft-nn #[cfg(test)])\n\n#### test_unsupported_register_includes_module_type\n- Call register_parameter on a module that doesn't override it (e.g., ReLU)\n- Assert the error message contains \"ReLU\"\n- Assert the error message contains \"register_parameter\"\n\n#### test_unsupported_register_buffer_includes_module_type\n- Same for register_buffer on a leaf module\n\n#### test_all_modules_have_type_name\n- For each major module type (Linear, Conv1d, Conv2d, LSTM, Sequential, etc.):\n  - Construct an instance\n  - Assert module_type_name() returns a non-empty string\n  - Assert module_type_name() does NOT contain \"Module\" alone (should be specific)\n\n#### test_module_type_name_matches_struct_name\n- For a selection of modules, verify that module_type_name() matches the Rust struct name\n- E.g., Linear::module_type_name() == \"Linear\"\n\n#### test_sequential_register_parameter_succeeds\n- Verify that Sequential (which DOES support register_parameter) still works correctly\n- Construct a Sequential, register a parameter, verify it appears in named_parameter_slots_own()\n\n### E2E validation\n- Run `rch exec -- cargo test -p ft-nn` — all existing + new tests pass\n- Run `rch exec -- cargo clippy -p ft-nn --all-targets -- -D warnings` — clean\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- Error messages include the module type name (e.g., \"ReLU does not support register_parameter\")\n- ALL Module implementations have module_type_name()\n- 5+ new tests covering the enriched error paths\n- Existing tests still pass\n- Clippy clean\n\n## Risk\nMedium — this adds a required trait method to ~40 implementations. Use grep to find all `impl Module for` blocks. Each just needs one line added. Can be parallelized with subagents.\n\n## Dependencies\nNone — isolated change within ft-nn.","status":"closed","priority":3,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-02T23:23:05.244308597Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-03T00:26:31.066854625Z","closed_at":"2026-04-03T00:26:31.066605804Z","close_reason":"ModuleRegistrationError::Unsupported now carries module_type context, default Module registration methods report std::any::type_name::<Self>(), and ft-nn test plus workspace check/clippy passed via rch","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
